The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                         NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 Jammu, July 14 (PTI): The Shri Amarnath Shrine Board has dropped plans to install a marble Shiv Lingam at the entrance to the cave shrine following a high court notice.          
	A group of Kashmiris had filed a petition saying the installation of a marble lingam at the cave would amount to sacrilege.                   
	Vadodara (PTI): An ICICI bank recovery agent was arrested on Sunday for snatching a gold chain from a woman near a cinema in Bhiwandi near Mumbai. Police also found gold bangles, chains and necklaces from Tabrez Jafri.                   Ranchi (PTI): Jharkhand transport secretary Sajal Chakraborty on Monday became the first serving IAS officer to be convicted in the 1990s fodder scam by a special CBI court. It also sentenced 10 women, all fodder suppliers, to three years in jail. Chakrabortys sentence will be pronounced on Tuesday.                   
	Mumbai (PTI): The Maharashtra government on Monday told Bombay High Court it would not implement the 70:30 formula during admissions in junior colleges in this academic year. The formula, under which 70 per cent seats in district colleges was to be reserved for home students, was challenged on the ground that it was biased against those from outside.                   
	Melbourne (PTI): Thirty-two Catholic pilgrims from India have gone missing during a stopover in the New Zealand capital, Auckland. They were on their way to Sydney where they would have met the Pope at the World Youth Day celebrations.                                                                                                                         
